g.text: to make clear what im saying
i know this is out of spec
for usbc. it is bad and i should not do it
and i am sorry, but i do not need my cables to be
able to switch orientation so it shouldn't be a problem? i think?
leads out to some power source, cable is long to illustrate that it has slack.
idea is - spring stores energy when i slot the thing in, so when I press on the thing
later to open it back up, spring reaches a point where the energy can be released
and then it springs forward, opening my drawer.
in this design, i take the port with it, because i dont think i can spring forward something
that is actually connected to a usbc port at the time.
i dont need the spring to move it a ton, i just need it to move the whole system enough
that i can get my fingers into the cubby, so i can pull the cubby fully open, disconnecting it from the usbc port.
as far as the spring lets it.
